I agree with DarkStuff in that this article basically requires you to read the whole canon before you can understand the interview log, but I honestly don't care if I'm gonna be completely honest. Anything coming out from EoD is a treat for me as it is one of my favorite canons by a long shot, and I don't necessarily think that every single SCP article that was made for a canon must absolutely stand on its own. While a regular ol' article or one with haphazard crosslinks must be able to stand on its own, canons have the responsibility of furthering the plot, and this SCP serves the function of making the readers start to dislike the Ethics Committee in EoD if they did not already. If this was the first EoD skip that I had ever read, then perhaps I wouldn't have immediately hopped into the canon like I did when I read , but I think that's okay if it serves a purpose within the canon, which this article certainly does.







